2026-04-21 01:30:37 | INFO     | DiagnosticAssistantLLM | OUTPUT: suggestion_type='hypothesis' action_type=None action_target=None action_description=None suspected_components=['timing potentiometer on control (ambient sensor) module'] hypothesis_explanation='The symptom was a periodic on–off cycling of the lamp, about every 20 seconds, while the power supply indicator LED remained steadily on. This points to the control (ambient sensor) module deliberately opening and closing the relay, rather than an intermittent connection or power problem.\n\nAdjusting only the timing potentiometer changed the behavior, and after sweeping its setting the lamp now remains steadily on with no internal faults reported. No components were replaced and no other parts were adjusted, yet the undesired cycling disappeared. This indicates that the underlying hardware was healthy and the root cause was the misadjusted timing potentiometer, which had been set to a value that caused the control circuit to periodically toggle the relay in the present ambient conditions.\n\nTherefore the fault was not a damaged component but an incorrect configuration of the timing potentiometer in the control module; restoring a proper setting resolves the issue.'
