description: Measure the DC supply voltage and ground/reference continuity at multiple points within the control module (e.g., at the comparator/op‑amp supply pins, relay driver supply, and any internal regulators or decoupling capacitors) while the system runs, checking for any periodic drops, oscillations, or poor ground connections that could drive the module into an unstable/oscillating state every ~20 seconds., outcome='The control module is in an unstable/oscillating state during measurement, but all checked components and cables show nominal continuity/resistance. Supply-related voltages at the sensors, potentiometers, relay, and control cables are present and roughly consistent with the expected low (~0–0.03 V) and high (~5.9–11.9 V) levels at their respective terminals, with no polarity inversion detected between the labeled (+) and (−) cables.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=405.0, cost_breakdown=[('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module timing/sensitivity network (RC components around the comparator),
description: Inspect and electrically test the discrete passive components that set the timing and sensitivity in the control module (the resistors and capacitors in series/parallel with the timing and sensitivity potentiometers). Using the inspection panel, identify the timing capacitor(s) and associated resistors, then measure their capacitance, leakage, and connections to confirm they match design values and are not intermittently open/shorted. Also verify that no unintended feedback or coupling path exists (e.g., via a miswired or wrong‑value component) that could cause long‑period oscillation even with correct supply and sensor operation., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Test -> control (ambient sensor) module timing/sensitivity passive components,
description: Using the inspection panel, individually test the timing capacitor(s) and associated fixed resistors in the RC network (not the potentiometers) with supported operations: measure_voltage across each during operation, test_continuity of their connections, and, if possible, measure their equivalent resistance/leakage to detect any intermittent short or open that could drive the comparator into long‑period oscillation despite normal supply and sensor behavior., outcome='The sensor bias resistor measures nominal resistance at 10 kΩ with normal continuity, and the measured branch current of 0.000591 A is consistent with the observed voltage across it. No polarity inversion is indicated in the reported connections or measurements.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=90.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('measure_voltage', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('measure_current', 20.0), ('test_continuity', 20.0), ('close_inspection_panel', 5.0)], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> external ambient-light conditions around control (ambient sensor) module,
description: Visually inspect and note the ambient light level around the light sensor (e.g., room lights on/off, daylight variation, any blinking or periodically changing light sources near the sensor, or shadows cast by the stacked modules). Check specifically whether any external light source or periodic obstruction could be changing the light sensor input roughly every 20 seconds and driving the module into its reported oscillating state., outcome='The requested action could not be mapped to any recognized diagnostic operation. Only actions from the available action list are supported (e.g. measure_voltage, test_continuity, inspect_connections, verify_repair, …).\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=0.0, cost_breakdown=[], simplified_outcome=None), DiagnosticActionResult(action=
name: Observe -> control (ambient sensor) module light sensor area and nearby indicators,
description: Inspect the physical area around the control module’s light sensor and any status/indicator LEDs on the module via the inspection panel, looking for any internal blinking indicator or periodically changing light source that could be illuminating the sensor roughly every 20 seconds and causing the reported oscillation., outcome='The ambient light sensor and the PSU green status LED both appear normal, with no observable internal faults; the PSU LED is steadily lit. The internal indicator lamp on the load module is also lit, has no observable internal fault, and is connected in parallel with the main load to reflect branch voltage conditions. No internal blinking or periodically changing light source with a ~20-second period was observed near the light sensor.\nCurrent persistent circuit state [differences with the starting state]:\nNo circuit-level changes introduced by diagnostics.', precise_action_cost=40.0, cost_breakdown=[('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('observe_component', 10.0), ('open_inspection_panel', 5.0), ('observe_component', 10.0)], simplified_outcome=None)] 
